Rating: 4
Great summer dessert! Used my blueberries that we had picked this summer and had frozen. Doubled and used a 9x13 pan, no need to double crust (maybe 1-1/2) because I had dough left over. Cut sugar by a 1/4 cup. Will keep as a favorite for blueberries!

Rating: 3
The cobbler was good but way too sweet for our taste. If I made it again in would use half as much sugar in the blueberries. I used small ramekins and the recipe made 8 with enough topping left over to make two scones.

