Rating: 4
Easy and delicious. My guests loved it. If you have leftovers top your chilled cobbler with Greek yogurt for breakfast. I used Fage 0%, very yummy. I'm sure it would be good reheated too but since it was warm outside when I ate this for breakfast I decided to eat this cold from a night in the fridge.

Rating: 4
This got rave reviews. Easy and really delicious. We made it with fresh Michigan blueberries that were tart and flavorful but not too sweet, so the cobbler wasn't obnoxiously sugary. The topping (I made it with sour cream) was much better than the usual crumbly cobbler topping.

